    "summary": "makes cats jam to the rhythm of music discs :3",
    "description": "<img src=\"https://github.com/shmove/cat_jam/blob/1.21.2/cat_jam_banner.gif?raw=true\" width=\"900\">\n<img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/V66sgZTs/divider.png\" alt=\"line separator\">\n\n<center><h3>üé∂ About üé∂</h3></center>\n\n<center><p>\ncat_jam is a clientside mod for Fabric, Forge & NeoForge that makes cats jam to the rhythm of music discs :3<br>\nEach disc has a set routine so cats will always jam accordingly. <br>\nPost any issues or requests on the issues board, or contact me at @shmove on discord. :catjam:<br>\n</p></center>\n\n<img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/V66sgZTs/divider.png\" alt=\"line separator\">\n\n<center><p>\n<h3>üéº Compatibility üéº</h3>\ncat_jam has basic compatibility with all mods that use the vanilla jukebox, with cats doing a simple all-fitting jam for all unknown tracks. The mods listed here have compatibility either through <strong>completely unique and customised jams</strong> per disc or through integration with a custom music system.\n</p></center>\n\n<center>\n<p><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/dwdsb\"><strong>Discs Where Discs Shouldn't Be</strong></a><br>\nAll 14 discs supported. These are some of my favourite modded discs ever, highly recommend!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/alexs-mobs\"><strong>Alex's Mobs</strong></a><br>\nBoth Daze & Thime supported.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/quark\"><strong>Quark</strong></a><br>\nEndermosh supported, and cats ignore ambient discs.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/supplementaries\"><strong>Supplementaries</strong></a><br>\nBoth Heave Ho! and the secret disc supported.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://modrinth.com/mod/audioplayer\"><strong>AudioPlayer</strong></a><br>\nCats do a simple all-fitting jam to all custom AudioPlayer discs. <strong>(>=1.19.2 only)</strong></p>\n</center>\n\n<img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/V66sgZTs/divider.png\" alt=\"line separator\">\n\n<center><h3>üéπ Want custom jams for the discs from your mod? üéπ</h3></center>\n\n<center><p>\nPlease get in touch! I'd be happy to work on that for you.<br>\nYou can also try and create the routines yourself and I will gladly add them!\n</p></center>\n\n<img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/V66sgZTs/divider.png\" alt=\"line separator\">\n\n<center><h3>üé¨ Previews üé¨</h3></center>\n\n<center>\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/AgZiUPp4T80\"></iframe>\n<p>(thank you <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@Jayfrey23\">Jayfrey</a> for this wonderful showcase video!!)</p>\n<br>\n</center>\n\n<center>\n<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vhApJRNKKUk\"></iframe><br><br>\n</center>\n\n<img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/V66sgZTs/divider.png\" alt=\"line separator\">\n\n<center><h3>üíï Support üíï</h3></center>\n\n<center>\n<p><a href=\"https://billing.rocketnode.com/aff.php?aff=150447\"><img src=\"https://i.postimg.cc/J4JXjtZv/rocketnode.jpg\"></a></p>\n<p>Consider hosting with RocketNode! By <strong>clicking above</strong> and using my promo-code, you'll be supporting me directly and getting 35% off enterprise grade Minecraft server hosting at the same time :3</p>\n</center>",
