    "description": "# Clean Tooltips\n\n[![](https://img.shields.io/discord/574476444366012420?label=Discord&color=393939&labelColor=5865F2&style=for-the-badge&logo=discord&logoColor=white)](https://discord.gg/cwqwNx3TGE)\n[![](https://img.shields.io/endpoint.svg?url=https%3A%2F%2Fshieldsio-patreon.vercel.app%2Fapi%3Fusername%3Dmandalacreations%26type%3Dpatrons&style=for-the-badge&color=393939&labelColor=FF424D&logoColor=FFFFFF)](https://www.patreon.com/mandalacreations)\n\nEver felt like the default tooltips could be fancied up a bit? Then this is exactly what you're looking for.\n\n¬†\nMainly the mod overhauls the way enchantments get displayed in the tooltip:\n\n* they now have their own \"Enchantents:\" subcategory\n* color coding to easier tell apart good enchantments (green) and curses (red)\n* max level enchantments will be displayed in gold¬†\n* curses are always ordered at the bottom of the list\n\n\nWith the mod installed:¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬† ¬†Without the mod installed (Vanila):\n\n![](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/vMoHe8uI/images/c14297cb39a23c1a2a5f50d90c6d23efe681ea20.png)\n\n¬†\n\nBesides that, other parts got also improved:\n\n\n* the color line on dyed items now actually shows the used color¬†\n* damaged items show their remaining durability in the tooltip¬†\n\n![](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/vMoHe8uI/images/fda90f7739ffda59decfeffa64e4cb8288d852c3.png)\n\n\nWe have many more ideas on how tooltips could be improved for future updates. Besides adding new features, the next updates will also add many configurability options.¬†\n\n\n![](https://i.imgur.com/4r5WLBc.png)\n![](https://i.imgur.com/fpeqHMC.png)",
