    "slug": "numismatics",
    "name": "Create: Numismatics",
    "summary": "Aesthetic & Functional Create styled currency mod",
    "description": "[![discord-plural](https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@intergrav/devins-badges@3/assets/cozy/social/discord-plural_vector.svg)](https://discord.gg/md78MGbEfK)\n\n# Create: Numismatics\n\nNumismatics is a brand-new currency mod that boasts easy-to-use systems for simple shops as well as leaving room for your wildest redstone-capitalism dreams.\n\n## Features\n\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/vendor.png\" width=80/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/creative_vendor.png\" width=80/>\n\n### Vendor\nQuick buying or selling of items, designed for compact player-run shops.\n\nCreative version allows server admins to setup infinitely-refilling shops.\n\n<br/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/bank_terminal.png\" width=80/>\n\n### Bank Terminal\nAccess your virtual bank account to deposit and withdraw coins.\n\n<br/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/andesite_depositor.png\" width=80/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/brass_depositor.png\" width=80/>\n\n### Depositor\nSet a price and the depositor will emit a 1 redstone tick pulse once a player deposits money, either by having coins in their inventory or by using a card.\n\n<br/>\n\n### Coins\nThe backbone of the mod, with 6 different coins of various values to choose from.\n\n| Spur   | Bevel   | Sprocket | Cog      | Crown  | Sun     |\n| ------ | ------- | -------- | -------- | ------ | ------- |\n| 1 spur | 8 spurs | 16 spurs | 64 spurs | 8 cogs | 64 cogs |\n| ![Spur](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/spur.png) | ![Bevel](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/bevel.png) | ![Sprocket](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/sprocket.png) | ![Cog](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/cog.png) | ![Crown](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/crown.png) | ![Sun](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/sun.png) |\n\n\n<br/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/red_card.png\" width=80/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/red_id_card.png\" width=80/>\n\n### Bank and ID Cards\nBank Cards can be placed in a Depositor or Vendor to have funds go directly into the associated account. Additionally, using a Bank Card on a Vendor or Depositor extracts funds from your account instead of taking coins from your inventory.\n\nID Cards are used to allow other players access to Numismatics' protected blocks (Vendors, Depositors, and Blaze Bankers), allowing you to easily give access to your business partners.\n\n<br/><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Layers-of-Railways/ImageDump/main/numismatics/blaze_banker.png\" width=80/>\n\n### Blaze Banker\nIs one bank account not enough for your ~~tax evasion~~ business needs? Create another and use ID Cards to allow your business partners to withdraw funds.",
