    "summary": "A decoration mod themed around ports and markets",
    "description": "![Dusty Decoration's logo](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/cached_images/124a7dbad4236ab40a5d8cf2f4031ca3c12ac634.png)\n\nDusty Decorations adds many rustic blocks for you to decorate your world with.\n\n![Screenshot of a minecraft market, with 2 stalls in front of a sea-side house. Modded blocks such as papers and jars litter the floor and stalls.](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/KgFOuaiZ/images/20b82dc68b444e4a27bff115f629fc1b5ffb4d1f.png)\n\n**NOTE: 1.20.1+ versions require Geckolib**\n\nMost blocks are themed around ports and markets, with a rustic and feel. Some of the included blocks are: Barrels of food, pots and pans, buoys, jars, books, scattered paper and posters, awnings, and more.\n\nMany of the blocks have randomized textures and models to keep builds from seeming repetitive, and some have small features such as climbable rope. All blocks are craftable in survival with simple recipes.\n\n<details>\n  <summary>List of blocks</summary>\n  \n\n\nFood Barrels: Includes variants for most food types, such as potatoes, apples, cod, and berries\n\nHanging Fish: fish hanging from rope, designed to connect to above blocks such as chains and rope\n\nShelves: Can be used to place blocks on, or as tables, building supports, and more\n\nHanging Knives: Perfect for Kitchens\n\nPosters and Scattered Paper: Over 10 randomized textures to fill up your walls and floors\n\nRope: Rotatable and climbable\n\nJars: Random textures and models, perfect for filling up space\n\nCorrugated Metal: A rusty metal suited for a old roof, and it includes a awning\n\nWedged knives and cutting boards: A knife wedged into a surface or cutting board. The cutting board is also placeable separately\n\nCluttered shelf and Small Bookshelf: A small shelf with randomized textures. Can have books or jars on it\n\nBooks and Book Stack. Books to either place on a shelf or stack on top of each other\n\nPaper Stack: Can be stacked on shelves or itself\n\nAwnings: Can be used on top of windows or with carpet roofs\n\nLife Preservers, Anchors, Large and Small Glass Buoys, and Treasure Map: Some seaside decor\n\nWooden Buoys: Colorful buoys hanging from rope, great decoration to hang on walls\n\nCooking Pots, Frying Pans, Pots And Pans Stack, and Placeable Bowl: Great decorations for a crowded kitchen\n\n\n</details>\n\nAvailable for Forge 1.19.3 and 1.19.2\n\nor Fabric 1.20.1\n\nFabric version coded by Mhaks\n\n1.20.1 Forge and NeoForge versions coded by RedKoopa (marioz170)",
