    "name": "LambDynamicLights - Dynamic Lights",
    "summary": "Adds dynamic lights to Minecraft as the most feature-complete and optimized dynamic lighting mod.",
    "description": "# LambDynamicLights\n\n\n[![GitHub license](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-Lambda%20License-c7136d?style=flat-square)](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.2/LICENSE)\n![Environment: Client](https://img.shields.io/badge/environment-client-1976d2?style=flat-square)\n[![Mod loader: Fabric]][fabric] [![Mod loader: NeoForge]][neoforge] \n\nThe most feature-complete and optimized dynamic lighting mod.\n\n## üìñ What's this mod?\n\nIt's dark outside, extremely dark...\nYou can't see a lot in the darkness, you wish you had a torch,\nor a lantern to hold and see in the light...\n\nAnd this is now possible with this mod as it adds dynamic lights to the game.\nYou can see in the darkness thanks to your torch now!\n\nThis mod adds dynamic lights to Minecraft. Dynamic lights are lights created by an entity holding an\nitem which makes light as a block, or created by an entity on fire, etc.\n\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xew0s2TwZ84\" title=\"Trailer\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen>\n</iframe>\n\nSearching other mods to replace OptiFine? [Check out this list!](https://optifine.alternatives.lambdaurora.dev/)\n\n## ‚úÖ Features:\n\n- Dynamic lighting.\n- Settings to select how smoothly the dynamic lighting updates.\n- Any entity holding an item which emits light will emit light!\n  - Item lighting can be customized through resource-packs and can work with modded items!\n  - Some items like torches, soul torches, etc. will not light up in water.\n- Various entities will naturally emit light, like:\n  - Allays\n  - Blazes\n  - Fireballs\n  - Glow squids\n  - Magma cubes\n  - Spectral arrows\n- Burning entities emit light.\n- Quick and simple API for developers and resource pack makers.\n  - Check out [the documentation][documentation] for more details!\n- And more!\n\n## üñºÔ∏è Screenshots\n\n### Items emit light\n\nDropped items which already emit light as a block, will also dynamically emit light!\n\n![Dropped lantern](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/lantern_study.png)\n\n### Held items emit light\n\nLight is emitted when entities hold light emitting items.\n\n![Torch](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/torch.png)\n![Fox holding glowberries](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/fox_holding.png)\n\n### Fire! Fire! Fire!\n\nAny entity on fire will emit light!\n\n![An Aurora is on fire!](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/fire.png)\n![Arrow on fire!](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/fire_arrow.png)\n\n### Explosion imminent!\n\nCreepers can make their imminent explosions more apparent through a progressive emission of light!\n\n![Quick! Need to protect myself from this Creeper!](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/creeper.png)\n\n### Glow Squids!\n\nThe infamous glow squids finally glow in your world!\n\n![A group of glow squids](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/glow_squid.png)\n\n### Guardian Lasers!\n\nWait... what? **Lasers?!** They do pack a punch...\n\n![light levels](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/guardian_laser.png)\n\n### Fireflies\n\nFireflies particle will emit light as they fly!\n\n![Fireflies](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/fireflies.png)\n\n### Configuration GUI\n\nAs of v4.0.0.\n\n![Configuration GUI](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/settings_main.png)\n![Entities Configuration](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/1.21.8/assets/settings_entities.png)\n\n## ‚ùì Usage\n\nUsing this mod is very simple!\n\nOn Fabric, install it in your mods folder along with [Fabric API] and [ModMenu], (and [Sodium] if wanted for better performances).  \nOn NeoForge, install it in your mods folder (and along with [Sodium] if wanted for better performances).\n\nIt will work as-is. If you want, you can configure the mod through its settings screen by heading to the video settings or via the mods list.\n\nNeed help? Come check out [my Discord server][LambdAurora Discord].\n\n## üî• Integrations and Compatibility\n\n- [Sodium] is recommended for better performances.\n- [Beltborne Lanterns] to equip a lantern on a belt and have a light source on yourself at all time!\n- [Illuminated] a flashlight mod using LambDynamicLights.\n\n## ‚ùì Is there an API? How to use it as a developer?\n\n[Check out this in-depth documentation][documentation].\n\n## ‚ùì How does it work internally?\n\n[Check out this document I've written on the fundamentals of it](https://github.com/LambdAurora/LambDynamicLights/blob/1.21/HOW_DOES_IT_WORK.md).\n\n\n\n\n[fabric]: https://fabricmc.net \"Fabric home page\"\n[Mod loader: Fabric]: https://img.shields.io/badge/modloader-Fabric-1976d2?style=flat-square&logo=data:image/png;base64,\n[Fabric API]: https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api \"Fabric API Modrinth page\"\n[neoforge]: https://neoforged.net \"NeoForge home page\"\n[Mod loader: NeoForge]: https://img.shields.io/badge/modloader-NeoForge-1976d2?style=flat-square&logo=data:image/png;base64,\n[ModMenu]: https://modrinth.com/mod/modmenu \"Mod Menu Modrinth page\"\n[Sodium]: https://modrinth.com/mod/sodium \"Sodium Modrinth page\"\n[Beltborne Lanterns]: https://modrinth.com/mod/beltborne-lanterns \"Beltborne Lanterns Modrinth page\"\n[Illuminated]: https://modrinth.com/mod/illuminated \"Illuminated Modrinth page\"\n[documentation]: https://lambdaurora.dev/projects/lambdynamiclights/docs/v4/ \"The documentation page of LambDynamicLights\"\n[LambdAurora Discord]: https://discord.lambdaurora.dev",
