    "summary": "Adds a 100% customizable welcome & update screen on world join.",
    "description": "<h1><p align=\"center\">\nWelcome Screen\n</p></h1>\n<p align=\"center\">\nAllows to add welcome and \"What's new\" update screens, fully customizable using FancyMenu. Great for accessibility and showing important information.\n</p>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\nRequires <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/necronomicon\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Necronomicon API</a> and <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/fancymenu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">FancyMenu</a>.\n</p>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\nUpdate Screen requires <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/better-compatibility-checker\" rel=\"nofollow\">Better Compatibility Checker</a>.\n</p>\n\n---\n\n## ‚≠ê Features ‚≠ê\n\n### **Welcome Screens**  \nWelcome Screens are only shown one time, once a player installs the modpack and joins a world or server, then it no longer shows. Useful to show important information, like keybinds, etc.\n\n**Example:**  \n![Welcome Screen Example](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvb-uy/cdn/340ef7daa553e2889b949340210fefd076da6e48/desc/welcomescreen/example.png)\n\n### **Update Screens**  \nUpdate Screens will appear when the user updates the modpack directly from their launcher, and serve as a way to showcase important changes in the newer version, etc.\n\n---\n\n## üí´ Config üí´\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvb-uy/cdn/340ef7daa553e2889b949340210fefd076da6e48/desc/welcomescreen/config.png\" alt=\"Config Example\" width=\"800\">\n</p>",
